*Composing methods — exception handling with <<<escalations>>>

  A step that throws a checked exception can have its escalation handled by another step in the same composition:

+--
call:
  class: com.example.RiskyLogic
  escalations:
    java.io.IOException: handleError

handleError:
  class: com.example.ErrorLogic
+--

  The exception becomes the <<<@Parameter>>> of the handler step.  If no per-step escalation is configured, the exception propagates to Spring's normal exception-handling infrastructure (<<<@ExceptionHandler>>>, <<<@ControllerAdvice>>>, etc.).

  A top-level <<<composition:>>> block handles escalations from any step in the file:

+--
composition:
  escalations:
    java.io.IOException: handleError

call:
  class: com.example.RiskyLogic

handleError:
  class: com.example.ErrorLogic
+--



